<Sequential id="writing_frequency_demo" title="Writing Process Journal 1" launchable="true">
    <Vertical id="wpj1_Introduction">
       <Markdown>
            # Writing Process Journal 1
            **Frequency of Past Writing Experiences**
            
            The purpose of this journal assignment is to get you thinking about how often
            you do various kinds of writing. What are your writing habits? What kinds of
            writing do you do often -- or rarely?
            
            Your writing experiences have almost certainly shaped your expectations
            about writing. So it's a good idea to take some time to reflect about
            those experiences and use that as a springboard into developing your
            own identity as a writer.
            
            The next several screens ask you to estimate how often you perform many
            different writing tasks, either for school or outside of school.
            
            You will get a chance to ask the computer to compare your responses to those
            of a typical student in this class.
            
            At the end, the computer will analyze your writing habits. It may be wrong,
            so read the analysis carefully! Then you will have a chance to react to
            what the computer wrote (and your own writing experiences, as reflected
            in the survey questions) by writing two reflective journal entries.
            
       </Markdown>
    </Vertical>
